1.
Redo the load of database.

Instead of loading database in settings.class.php, create a load.php file that loads everything that's nessecery.
Make the database function to load as a global class.

Example of code to load the database:

function require_wp_db() {
	global $wpdb;

	require_once( ABSPATH . WPINC . '/wp-db.php' );
	if ( file_exists( WP_CONTENT_DIR . '/db.php' ) )
		require_once( WP_CONTENT_DIR . '/db.php' );

	if ( isset( $wpdb ) ) {
		return;
	}

	$wpdb = new wpdb(DB_USER, DB_PASSWORD, DB_NAME, DB_HOST);
}
